    <p>SCOTT DETROW, BYLINE: The starting point in the conversation Democrats are having with themselves right now is this - Republicans in Congress spent almost all of the past eight years opposing President Obama, and they seem to have reaped a lot of political rewards for the block opposition. House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi is quick and careful to reject that approach.</p>
