    <p>GREENE: Why?</p>
    <p>KELLY: I think the concern is that it is a general divorced from his troops. I mean, the DNI does not send spies into the field. It does not have case officers working on the front lines in Iran or China or Russia or any of the other places that the U.S. is trying to spy on. It's supposed to hover above and coordinate the work of the agencies that do do that. So it is -</p>
    <p>GREENE: Take the broad view - but not hands-on.</p>
