    <p>SIMON: Citizens are very grateful for that quick action, I'm sure. To what do you attribute the confusion between camel and llama?</p>
    <p>WEEMS: (Laughter) Well, that I don't know. When the dispatcher called me, she was laughing. And she's like, yeah, we've gotten a call of a baby camel in the road and she said, no, we think it's a llama. And I guess someone's not - just like our deputies, they aren't trained in South American camelid identification.</p>
    <p>SIMON: Yeah. You're going to - you're going to take care of that in the future, sir?</p>
