    <p>GARCIA-NAVARRO: Yes.</p>
    <p>DEARDEN: That's Jesus, not Cheesus (ph). And anyway, so that is what it's meant to mean. But also as part of modern Christmasing (ph) that we do with trees and decorations, it's the night you're meant to get rid of all your Christmas decorations because if you keep them up, it's bad luck.</p>
    <p>GARCIA-NAVARRO: It's bad luck.</p>
    <p>DEARDEN: Vegetation will not grow. Your crops will not grow, and you'll have a terrible year.</p>
    <p>GARCIA-NAVARRO: You'll be cursed.</p>
    <p>DEARDEN: You'll be cursed essentially.</p>
    <p>GARCIA-NAVARRO: Now, this is my first week at WEEKEND EDITION SUNDAY. And I heard this pitch, and I was like - why? What was the sort of compelling reason here for this?</p>
    <p>DEARDEN: Well, I will tell you why it is unbelievably compelling.</p>
    <p>GARCIA-NAVARRO: OK.</p>
    <p>DEARDEN: Because I was cursed.</p>
    <p>GARCIA-NAVARRO: You were cursed?</p>
