    <p>SIMON: I'm told you've done a 103 sweaters.</p>
    <p>BARSKY: Yes. That's correct.</p>
    <p>SIMON: That's a lot of wool, a lot of stitches, isn't it?</p>
    <p>BARSKY: Yes, probably millions by now.</p>
    <p>SIMON: Do you know what you're going to knit next?</p>
    <p>BARSKY: Yes because Groundhog Day is coming up in early February, I'm thinking of making a sweater with a groundhog on it.</p>
    <p>SIMON: Oh, that sounds adorable. You must get requests at this point. You've become pretty famous.</p>
    <p>BARSKY: Yes. I'm flooded with requests, so many I can't even see all of them.</p>
    <p>SIMON: Yeah. Do you ever fulfill any?</p>
    <p>BARSKY: I've thought about it before, but I've realized early on a long time ago that it's not practical for me to be a human sweater mill.</p>
