    <p>TEIXEIRA: (Through interpreter) I was bitten by a piranha a long time ago when I was out fishing.</p>
    <p>REEVES: He shows me a scar on his thumb. The bite did hurt, he says.</p>
    <p>TEIXEIRA: (Through interpreter) But then I had some beer, and the pain was gone.</p>
    <p>REEVES: Back at Manaus airport, it's time to choose a souvenir. I select a tambaqui. It's the size of a laptop and costs 12 bucks. My tambaqui thawed before I reached my home in Rio de Janeiro 10 hours later. But this airport gift fooled the family, and it was also quite delicious. Philip Reeves, NPR News, Rio de Janeiro.</p>
