    <p>INSKEEP: So Christian refugees ultimately would get in a lot more easily than people of other faiths, Muslims particularly?</p>
    <p>KEITH: That is the theory - that they are being persecuted overseas and that they would have priority.</p>
    <p>INSKEEP: OK.</p>
    <p>KEITH: There would also be a 30-day ban on immigration from seven countries, Iran, Iraq, Libya, Somalia, Syria, Yemen and Sudan. And President Trump was asked about that in an interview with Sean Hannity that aired last night on Fox News.</p>
    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF TV SHOW, "HANNITY")</p>
